  "text": "Silencing of THSD1 involved LOH and promoter hypermethylation in esophageal cancer cell lines and tumor tissues with gene expression down-regulation [CITATION_1] . We identified THSD1 as aberrantly methylated in CRC cell lines and CRC positive samples. THSD1 showed a tumor specific methylation with no abnormal methylation in non-cancerous tissues (Table II, Fig. 3C ). Moreover, low expression in tumor tissues rather than normal for THSD1 besides no significant correlation between methylation and mRNA expression suggests that downregulation of THSD1 in CRC specimens could be attributed to allelic deletion, or epigenetic events other than methylation of the CpG islands.",
